=Translation Cooperative=

A translation cooperative can be formed by a group of people with language translation abilities to better manage their own individual work as translators and to share the expenses of the administration of their business.

There are several different types of translation work available.  For some translators location may not be an issue as they might receive their work through email or the mail, whereas simultaneous translation and interpretation services often occur and depend on geographic proximity.

Translation cooperatives make for excellent worker owned cooperatives.  

